comments.body:
Most probably because of the deprecated:

```
public OpenAiChatModel(OpenAiApi openAiApi) {
	this(openAiApi, OpenAiChatOptions.builder().model(OpenAiApi.DEFAULT_CHAT_MODEL).temperature(0.7).build());
}
```
and  even tho you setup your chat options :
```
// Define request options by merging runtime options and default options
OpenAiChatOptions requestOptions = ModelOptionsUtils.merge(runtimeOptions, this.defaultOptions,
		OpenAiChatOptions.class);
```
https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ai/blob/main/models/spring-ai-openai/src/main/java/org/springframework/ai/openai/OpenAiChatModel.java
----

To configure the chat model use `OpenAiChatModel.Builder` or `OpenAiChatModel(OpenAiApi, OpenAiChatOptions, ToolCallingManager, RetryTemplate, ObservationRegistry)` .
